	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Who defines "frivolous"? Perhaps it's time to throw you in jail, Christabel. Certainly, posting to the message board is neither useful nor productive.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>That's right. But you've missed the entire point. Entertainment is not wrong. And frivolous entertainment is not wrong either. But if a thing can cause long term harm to people and offers nothing <u>more</u> than entertainment, then nobody is gonna suffer for losing it.<br />
<br />
Posting on this message board is frivolous. So is going out for a drive in your car. And so is listening to the radio. But there's no reason to prohibit people from doing any one of those things (no matter how compulsively they do them) since the public is served to a much greater extent by having them available.<br />
<br />
So to return to the dead horse... online gaming is in the first catgory and not the second.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
