	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><i>Originally posted by Christabel </i><br />
<b> So if you have a thing which, at it's best, is not capable of providing anything more than entertainment, but at its worst can be used by people to ruin their lives... </b><hr size="1" /></blockquote>What ever happened to being responsible for your own actions.  Even if that action ruins your life?  Where do we draw the line? Gaming lost you your job? McDonalds Fries made you fat?  Who is responsible for the lost job or the obesity? The company making the products or you indulging?<br />
<br />
People have to be responsible for their own actions.  End of story.  I personally think the Greek Government should just let the people "ruin their lives" with the gambling or gaming should just let them do it and in the end, NOT pick up their tab.  All they are doing is enabling people to become even more lazy and irresponsible by taking away their right to make the right choices.<br />
<br />
Personally I would rather be accountable for my choices and always have them rather then unaccountable and have no choices.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107896" target="_blank">~Calbrazan Deo'Cara</a> <br />
Tribunal Shamanette<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47541" target="_blank">~Calimayrn Anam'Cara</a><br />
