	<p>Ugh ... this gets worse.    "Definition of good: those things which produce more benefit than detriment" ... who decides this?<br />
<br />
You?  As a single person within a community?   <br />
The Greek government?     As the moral police for it's country as a whole?   Including the visitor/tourist?  It's population?    Controlling it's populist thoughts ... a very comforting idea.<br />
<br />
From Webster's on Draconian ... "of, relating to, or characteristic of Draco or the severe code of laws held to have been framed by him".   Notice that doesn't interpret what is a severe code of laws ... just that they are severe.    Creating a sweeping set of laws without careful consideration of the scope ... is Draconian.    Interpreting "Pacman" to be as morally corrupt as "Pacman does Dallas" is illogical.  At it's best it's lazy lawmaking ... at it's worse it's government gone mad.    Can anyone say "Big Brother".</p>
	
	
	
	
	
