	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />It's hypocritical to laud this move and still keep your EQ account. Sounds like the old drunk telling a bunch of 25-year olds that they shouldn't start drinking while swilling beer from a "40." <hr size="1" /></blockquote>Just because someone's a hypocrite doesn't mean they're not giving good advice. If an alcoholic tells me a sad tale of how he lost his job, wife and custody of his kids because of his problems, even though he might have scotch on his breath, I'll still take the lesson to heart.<br />
<br />
<br />
And as for banning games... I don't understand why playing a video game such as FIFA Soccer should be illegal even though you can step outside onto the street and play soccer. It's like saying the NYT on the web is illegal, but you can still read the print paper. It's really strange.</p>
	
	
	
