	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Just because someone's a hypocrite doesn't mean they're not giving good advice. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>Who says?  Firstly, my life experience may not be the same as the person who's giving it.  I.E. You could tell me the evils of video game additction, but if I'm not addicted or likely to become addicted, what's the advice worth?  secondly, how good could the advice be, if the person giving it isn't following it themselves?  Even the Bible says "take the great plank out of your own eye before removing the splinter from your brother's."   And thirdly, if the advice hasn't been asked, it aint wanted.  People don't want others to intrude on their decisions without first asking, it's REALLY rude and you lose your audience IMMEDIATELY.</p>
	
	
	
