</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Personally I would rather be accountable for my choices and always have them, rather then unaccountable and have no choices.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>That's probably my favorite quote of the thread. I was sorta being a goon this morning. But I think the issue of "accountability" is why I shruged at the greek government doing this, yet would object to our own government doing something similar. <br />
<br />
<i><b>quote</b></i>: <i>Nothing like this would ever happen in the US. And that's fine with me. - Christabel</i><br />
<i><b>quote</b></i>: <i>I support the right of the greek government to not pick up the tab... -Christabel</i><br />
<br />
I don't think it's right for a person to to knowingly make costly and destructive choices when his neighbor shares the bill for it. But based on the feedback people have given, I think the lesser evil might be to re-evaluate some of the government safety nets that create an unfair situation... than to micro-manage everyone's personal life from above. Runningwolf's examples were really good (censorship, etc). I guess things would get kinda bleak if government cracked down on <u>all</u> things that were "entertaining at best, but dangerous at worst."<br />
<br />
<img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="wink" smilieid="5" /></p>
	
	
	
	
	
